# End-to-End Checkout & Order Fulfillment — AI Coding Prompt

> **Project:** Marketplace (Next.js 16 + React 19 + PostgreSQL + Drizzle ORM + Better Auth + shadcn/ui)
> **Phase:** Phase 1 — MVP Go-Live (Exposure Online + Pickup in Store)
> **Scope:** 5 interdependent features implemented as a single cohesive checkout pipeline
> **Repository:** `~/marketplace` (monorepo: `apps/store`, `apps/admin`, `packages/db`)

---

## 1. Context & Overview

This prompt covers the **complete end-to-end checkout and order fulfillment flow** for a marketplace web app with a **pickup-in-store** model. Five Notion tickets are bundled into a single implementation session:

| # | Feature | Ticket |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Cart per Branch** — enforce 1 cart = 1 branch | Cart per Branch |
| 2 | **Checkout Pickup-Focused (Simplified Multi-step)** | Checkout Pickup |
| 3 | **Midtrans Integration — QRIS Only** | Midtrans |
| 4 | **Order Management — Admin List + Order Inquiry + Detail** | Order Management |
| 5 | **Pickup in Store — 6-Digit Text Code + Verification + Email + Time Validation** | Pickup in Store |

**High-level user story:**

1. Customer adds items to a **branch-scoped cart**.
2. Customer proceeds through a **4-step checkout**: contact info → pickup branch & time → QRIS payment → review & place order.
3. Payment processed via **Midtrans QRIS** with webhook verification.
4. Admin branch receives real-time notification, views the order, and confirms stock.
5. Upon successful payment, the system **auto-generates a 6-digit pickup code** and emails it to the customer.
6. Customer arrives at the branch, states the code; admin inputs it → order becomes **completed**.
7. Both **customer and admin** can view/inquire past transactions.

